// Per-session cooldown store for the guard-health critical-escalation banner
// (mt#3072).
//
// guard-health-escalation-detector.ts re-surfaces its CRITICAL banner on
// EVERY UserPromptSubmit turn while any guard remains critical — by design,
// per that module's own header comment: "a dead gate silently forgotten
// after one mention would defeat the point of an ESCALATING signal." That
// design intent is right for a signal that keeps CHANGING; it produces
// unbounded noise for one that doesn't. The standalone-duplicate-matcher
// incident (2026-07-19 -> 07-22, mt#3072) sustained ONE streak — 14
// check-skips, the last at 07-21T07:36Z — whose escalation state (guard
// name, streak, last message) never changed between failures, yet the
// banner re-injected on 385 of 697 turns (55%) across ~3 days: nothing
// distinguished "the same known cause, still true" from "something new the
// operator/agent needs to hear."
//
// This store lets the detector answer that question per session: has THIS
// exact critical-escalation signature (every currently-critical guard's
// name + its last failure's timestamp + message, see `escalationSignature`)
// already been surfaced to this conversation within the cooldown window? If
// so, suppress. The signal reappears the instant either (a) a NEW failure
// extends a streak or a guard newly turns critical (the composite signature
// changes), or (b) the cooldown elapses (a periodic reminder — preserving
// the "not silently forgotten" intent) — never suppressed forever.
//
// Scope is per-session (mirrors turn-end-scan-store.ts's per-session-file
// pattern), not global: a brand-new conversation that has never seen the
// warning still sees it at least once, even if some unrelated concurrent
// session's cooldown is already running. A shared/global file would also
// invite a read-modify-write race between concurrent sessions that
// turn-end-scan-store.ts's per-session layout was chosen specifically to
// avoid.
//
// @see .minsky/hooks/guard-health-escalation-detector.ts — the consumer
// @see .minsky/hooks/turn-end-scan-store.ts — the per-session-file precedent
// @see .minsky/hooks/guard-health.ts — GuardHealthSummary / getGuardHealthStateDir
